\subsection{Scalable Validation with Process Tensor MPOs}
\label{ssec:ptmpo}
To accurately simulate the global entropy dynamics of a long non-Markovian process, methods that can efficiently represent the multi-time correlation structure are required. Simple Matrix Product State (MPS) simulations that track entanglement across a single cut systematically underestimate the global entropy and fail to reproduce the Page turnover. To overcome this, we employ a Process-Tensor Matrix Product Operator (PT-MPO) approach~\cite{Strathearn:2018}, which represents the entire history of interactions as a compressed tensor network. The specific algorithm and its error certification are detailed in \cref{ssec:ptmpo_details}.

\paragraph{PT-MPO Validation.}
We implemented the scalable PT-MPO algorithm described in \cref{alg:ptmpo}. This method allows for the efficient and accurate computation of the global radiation entropy. As shown in \cref{fig:ptmpo_page}, the PT-MPO simulation successfully recovers the Page curve for a system with 20 emission steps, overcoming the limitations of simpler proxies.

