We analyzed the convergence and computational cost of the PT-MPO algorithm. \Cref{fig:ptmpo_error} shows the normalized RMSE relative to the ideal Page curve as a function of the bond dimension $\chi$. The error decreases systematically as $\chi$ increases, demonstrating that the PT-MPO provides a controllable approximation that converges to the exact dynamics. \Cref{tab:ptmpo_scaling} details the resource scaling, confirming that simulating HMC dynamics at a meaningful scale is computationally tractable. The complexity and error bounds are further analyzed in \cref{app:code}.

